    "text": "Your tracker puts your current sleep debt at 154 min — call it 2.6 h — accumulated over the window it tracks. That's real but very repayable, and the repayment plan matters more than the number: debt cleared gradually sticks, while one weekend binge mostly shifts your rhythm around. Your last week shows the pattern behind it — a 7-day average of 6.6 h against a nightly need of 7.7 h — so this isn't one bad night, it's a steady nightly shortfall. The single change I'd make: move bedtime earlier by half an hour every night this week while keeping your wake time fixed. That alone removes the biggest share of the nightly gap and starts draining the backlog within days. Treat the debt figure as an estimate, not a ledger — the direction of the trend is what you're managing.",
